<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-11512] Inconsistent isAttribute &amp; getAttribute behavior in Groovy 4 with traits</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-11512</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As a follow-up to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-10621&quot; title=&quot;Why isAttribute style getters have gone from groovy 4&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-10621&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-10621&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following class in groovy 4:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Testing {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;boolean&lt;/span&gt; deleted
} &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;will generate `getDeleted()` &amp;amp; `isDeleted`, but if a trait adds the property like this code:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
trait ParentTesting {
&#160;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;boolean&lt;/span&gt; deleted
}
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Testing &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;implements&lt;/span&gt; ParentTesting {
} &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It will generate only the isDeleted() and not the getDeleted() on the testing class.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, the behavior change mentioned in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-10621&quot; title=&quot;Why isAttribute style getters have gone from groovy 4&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-10621&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-10621&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is not mentioned in the Groovy 4 release notes.&#160; Can this behavior either be made consistent or reverted to pre-groovy 4 behavior?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
